HEADWORD: cæsar
<hw>c⟦ae⟧"sar</hw> <pr>(s⟦emac⟧"z⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L.]</ety> <def>A Roman emperor, as being the successor of
<person>Augustus C⟦ae⟧sar</person>. Hence, a kaiser, or emperor of
Germany, or any emperor or powerful ruler. See <er>Kaiser</er>,
<er>Kesar</er>, <er>Tsar</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Marlborough anticipated the day when he would be servilely
flattered and courted by <qex>C⟦ae⟧sar</qex> on one side and by Louis
the Great on the other.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

